	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><i>Originally posted by Gloriana </i><br />
<b>Hey Georgina, welcome to the board! <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
There are actually 10 shards for the Vex Thal Key Quest that drop throught SoL.  You need a unique shard from the following 10 zones:<br />
<br />
Dawnshroud Peak<br />
Seru<br />
Sraa<br />
Maiden's Eye<br />
Scarlet Desert<br />
The Grey<br />
Akheva<br />
The Deep<br />
Fungus Grove<br />
Acrylia<br />
<br />
(My bank is CRYING with all this VT key quest, not to mention various PoP quest crap!)<br />
<br />
It's like the stupid VP key quest on steriods!  To complete the quest, you also need a glowing orb of luclinite (drops from nearly all SoL boss mobs) a piece from the Emperor (you have to complete an additional 4 part key quest just to get TO the emperor) and another thing I can't remember. </b><hr size="1" /></blockquote>A sceptre frame which requires turning in an essence emerald to a mob in Akheva past the IV =)<br />
<br />
10 shards get combined in frame, makes a new 2 slot container.  Orb and emp peice get combined in 2 slot container to make your key and then your bank rejoices.<br />
<br />
Don't forget your melee need to do a 2 part quest to get weapons to even be able to hit the emp. And then you get to spend hours killing yard trash that can be upto lvl 66 and half or more is unmesable and probably half spawn a second mob when you kill them.<br />
<br />
As far as the actual questions. No clue just go up and solo your way around the catwalk. Personally I've gotten 4 shard drops in seru and I'm still not kos to them so it hasn't been bad for me. Even saw 2 drops consecutive mobs. On the other hand i've heard hours and hours for one shard from other people.</p>
	
	
	
